        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 6 at 7:22PM MDT until June 6 at 8:15PM MDT by NWS Goodland KS</headline>
        <description>SVRGLD

The National Weather Service in Goodland has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southern Wallace County in west central Kansas...
Northeastern Greeley County in west central Kansas...

* Until 815 PM MDT.

* At 721 PM MDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles southeast
of Weskan, or 10 miles southwest of Sharon Springs, moving
southeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Trained weather spotters reported 1 inch hail 4 miles
west of Weskan.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage
to roofs, siding, and trees.

* This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southern Wallace and northeastern Greeley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
